1.00	Boleslaw_Bierut	Bolesław Bierut	Bierut was born in Rury Jezuickie, now a part of Lublin, as the son of Henryk Rutkowski, a village teacher, and his wife Barbara Biernacka (Wojciech and Maria, according to IPN source). He later adopted the surname "Bierut" combining the first syllables of his parents' surnames. In 1918 he took courses at the Warsaw School of Economics, and in 1924–1930 went to Moscow, to be trained at the school of the Communist International.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/PL_Boles%C5%82aw_Bierut_%281892-1956%29.jpg/220px-PL_Boles%C5%82aw_Bierut_%281892-1956%29.jpg
